  "texts": [
    "4 is the particularly slow progress of observations taken in the r-band during the first 18 months of data-taking.",
    "This feature was traced to the queue scheduler, which was overly conservative for dark-time observations with strict seeing requirements.",
    "Changes to the scheduler in early 2013 addressed this problem and led to a speeding up of the dark-time KiDS observations.",
    "KiDZ acquisitionAs mentioned in Sects.",
    "3.1 and 3.1.1, DR5 includes observations made by the VST over deep spectroscopic survey fields that significantly enhance KiDS science."
  ]
